│ THOUGHT: The miscompile stems from InstCombine folding a select-of-fcmps into an fabs compare while propagating 'ninf' FMF to the synthesized fabs. This makes fabs poison on -inf even  │
│ when the original select would yield a benign false, increasing poison. The safe fix is to avoid carrying 'ninf' to the created fabs in foldSelectWithFCmpToFabs. I'll add a small       │
│ helper in that function to create fabs with FMF sanitized to clear no-infs, using IRBuilder's FastMathFlagsGuard to restore flags, and update all fabs creations in that function to use │
│ it.                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ applypatch << 'PATCH'                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ *** Begin Patch                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ *** Update File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                                                                                                                   │
│ @@                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│  static Instruction *foldSelectWithFCmpToFabs(SelectInst &SI,                                                                                                                            │
│                                               InstCombinerImpl &IC) {                                                                                                                    │
│ +  // When creating a synthesized fabs() while folding select-of-fcmp patterns,                                                                                                          │
│ +  // be careful with FastMathFlags propagation: 'ninf' coming from just one arm                                                                                                         │
│ +  // of the select can make the new fabs poison for -inf even if the original                                                                                                           │
│ +  // select would have produced a non-poison value. To avoid increasing poison,                                                                                                         │
│ +  // clear 'no-infs' on the created fabs.                                                                                                                                               │
│ +  auto CreateSafeFabs = [&](Value *X) -> Value * {                                                                                                                                      │
│ +    IRBuilderBase::FastMathFlagsGuard Guard(IC.Builder);                                                                                                                                │
